citeinfo.origin: National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) and U.S. Department of the Interior (DOI)
citeinfo.title: Marine Managed Areas

descript.abstract:
This GIS data set represents the federal marine managed areas including National Parks, National Marine Fisheries Service areas, National Estuarine Research reserves, National Marine Sanctuaries, and National Wildlife Refuges. FWRI downloaded these data from mpa.gov, managed by NOAA and DOI. This data set includes only the areas in the Gulf of Mexico, Caribbean, and southeastern US Atlantic Ocean. The internet site has additional areas in the Pacific, Great Lakes, and Northeast US, which were are not included in this file.
Executive Order 13158 mandates that the U.S. Departments of Commerce and the Interior "publish and maintain a list of Marine Protected Areas (MPAs) that meet the definition of MPA for the purposes of this order."
descript.purpose: It will allow users to examine various combinations of programs and selected MMA networks at local and regional levels throughout the coastal U.S.
descript.supplinf: Prior to July 1, 2004, the Fish and Wildlife Research Institute (FWRI) was known as the Florida Marine Research Institute (FMRI). The institute name has not been changed in historical data sets or references to work completed by the Florida Marine Research Institute. The institute name has been changed in references to ongoing research, new research, and contact information. The boundaries are created with the most recent and accurate boundary information available, but edges and/or borders of the boundaries may change due to natural land changes, site boundary modification or higher resolution maps. Therefore, the currency or accuracy of these boundaries cannot be guaranteed

attracc.attraccr: Special Projects assumed that the digital data sets originating from the NOAA Coastal Services Center were accurate. However, Special Projects tested the accuracy of the data by manual comparison of the source with hard copy print outs if available. Attributes were further verified using visual inspection.

dataqual.logic: All data sets were reprojected for integration into the MMA Inventory GIS. Environmental Systems Research Institute's (ESRIs) ArcGIS 8.x was used to complete all reprojections. Shorelines were then used to determine logical consistency. Geometry appears to be topologically clean.
dataqual.complete: The Marine Managed Areas Inventory of the United States data set contains boundaries for 25 National Estuarine Research Reserve System units. To view the MMA site criteria, please visit http:\\www.mpa.gov. Attribute information from the source has been simplified.

horizpa.horizpar: The MMA boundaries are approximate and are not to be used as legal definitions. Most of these data were created by delineating the boundaries off USGS 7.5 minute Topographic Maps at 1:24000 scale. Others were delineated from digital orthophotographs, collected at 1:12000 scale aerial photographs. Therefore, the horizontal accuracy is assumed to be within National Map Accuracy Standards, with a horizontal accuracy no greater than 45.6 feet at the 95% confidence level.

vertacc.vertaccr: Most of these data were created by delineating the boundaries off USGS 7.5 minute Topographic Maps at 1:24000 scale. Others were delineated from digital orthophotographs, collected at 1:12000 scale aerial photographs. Therefore, the vertical accuracy is assumed to be within National Map Accuracy Standards, with a vertical accuracy no greater than 11.9 feet at the 95% confidence level.

srcinfo.srccontr: The National Estuarine Research Reserve System digital boundaries were created as part of the Protected Areas Geographic Information System (PAGIS) project. An updated digital version of all 25 NERR sites boundaries were critical to the PAGIS project. The digital boundaries were delineated from management and research areas within the 25 Reserves. They were not based on legal definitions.

procstep.procdesc: FWRI staff downloaded these data and reselected for the area of interest (Gulf of Mexico, Caribbean, and southeastern US Atlantic). FWRI APPENDed the files for the different area types into one file, and added a TYPE attribute to distinguish the types.

overview.eaover: Executive Order 13158 mandates that the U.S. Departments of Commerce and the Interior "publish and maintain a list of Marine Protected Areas (MPAs) that meet the definition of MPA for the purposes of this order." To provide this information, an inventory of existing U.S. Marine Managed Areas (MMAs) is being developed. The inventory will support the development of the "list of MPA's" called for in the Executive Order 13158. Digital boundary files for the MMAs have been compiled from various agencies and formatted for use in a Geographic Information System (GIS) to produce a thematic series of maps for the Marine Managed Areas Inventory Atlas. This atlas is designed to enhance the understanding of the spatial relationships among the sites in the MMA Inventory. The Inventory will be used to inform federal agencies and all interested parties of the location of sites. It will help scientists and managers examine the design effectiveness of the current system of managed areas and determine which habitats are in need of improved or additional protection measures.
overview.eadetcit: The National Estuarine Research Reserve System digital boundaries were created as part of the Protected Areas Geographic Information System (PAGIS) project. An updated digital version of all 25 NERR sites boundaries were critical to the PAGIS project. The digital boundaries were delineated from management and research areas within the 25 Reserves. They were not based on legal definitions
